          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective Script Editor usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Set language:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Language</code> to the actual syntax so the status bar is informative.</li>
                <li><strong>Use ReadOnly:</strong> Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">ReadOnly</code> for scripts users should inspect but not modify.</li>
                <li><strong>Specific errors:</strong> Show <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Error Text</code> with a specific count or message ("3 syntax errors").</li>
                <li><strong>Use FullIDE only on dedicated pages:</strong> Ensure enough vertical space is available for the full IDE layout.</li>
                <li><strong>Use line numbers for debugging:</strong> Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">WithLineNumbers</code> whenever error messages reference line numbers.</li>
                <li><strong>Hide status bar sparingly:</strong> Toggle <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Show Status Bar=OFF</code> only for ultra-compact embeds.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Wrong language:</strong> Leave <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Language</code> as "TypeScript" for non-TypeScript scripts.</li>
                <li><strong>Disabled for read-only:</strong> Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Disabled</code> for read-only display &#8212; it implies unavailability.</li>
                <li><strong>Generic errors:</strong> Use generic text like "Error" without context.</li>
                <li><strong>FullIDE in small spaces:</strong> Embed FullIDE inside a small card or sidebar panel.</li>
                <li><strong>Hidden error status:</strong> Hide the status bar in Error state &#8212; the error count lives there.</li>
                <li><strong>Unnecessary line numbers:</strong> Add line numbers to Basic embeds where they add no informational value.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
