        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-accessibility" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <h2 id="accessibility" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for ensuring the Script Editor is accessible across assistive technologies and input methods.</p>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="keyboard-interaction" class="doc-h3">Keyboard Interaction</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>Tab</code></td><td>Inserts indentation (spaces per indent setting), does not move focus out of editor.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Shift+Tab</code></td><td>Decreases indentation.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Ctrl/&#8984;+A</code></td><td>Select all.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Ctrl/&#8984;+C</code></td><td>Copy selected text.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Ctrl/&#8984;+Z</code></td><td>Undo.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Ctrl/&#8984;+Shift+Z</code></td><td>Redo.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Ctrl/&#8984;+/</code></td><td>Toggle line comment.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Ctrl/&#8984;+Enter</code></td><td>Execute (when toolbar is present and Run is enabled).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Escape</code></td><td>Blur editor / return focus to parent context.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>F1</code></td><td>Open command palette (FullIDE only).</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="aria-attributes" class="doc-h3">ARIA Attributes &amp; Screen Reader Guidance</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Role:</strong> Wrap in <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">role="group"</code> with <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label="Script editor"</code> or <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-labelledby</code> referencing a heading.</li>
              <li><strong>Code area:</strong> The editable region should be a <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">contenteditable</code> div or a library-managed textarea with <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">role="textbox"</code> and <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-multiline="true"</code>.</li>
              <li><strong>ReadOnly:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-readonly="true"</code> on the code area; the "READ ONLY" badge should also be announced.</li>
              <li><strong>Disabled:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-disabled="true"</code> and remove from tab order (<code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">tabindex="-1"</code>). The purple/violet text tint is a visual cue only.</li>
              <li><strong>Error:</strong> Status bar should have <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-live="polite"</code> so error count changes are announced.</li>
              <li><strong>Toolbar buttons:</strong> Each button must have <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label</code> for icon-only buttons.</li>
              <li><strong>Focus ring:</strong> The 2px blue focus ring must not be overridden by global reset styles.</li>
              <li><strong>Contrast:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Text-Accent-Link</code> (keywords, blue) on the light editor background must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1).</li>
              <li><strong>Syntax colours:</strong> Do not rely solely on colour for syntax meaning &#8212; keywords should also be identifiable by context or font weight.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="focus-state-design" class="doc-h3">Focus State Design</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Visible focus indicator:</strong> The entire editor container receives a 2px blue border (<code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">#006AFF</code>) plus a blue shadow ring &#8212; this must not be overridden (WCAG 2.4.7).</li>
              <li><strong>Cursor indicator:</strong> A blinking text cursor appears inside the code area to signal input readiness.</li>
              <li><strong>Active-line highlight:</strong> The current cursor line receives a subtle background fill to provide visual context.</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top:24px;display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:center;padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
              <div class="se-container focus" style="width:120px;font-size:11px;">
                <div class="se-code-area" style="min-height:32px;padding:8px 10px;"><span class="kw">const</span> x = 1;</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:15px;color:var(--prism-text);">Focus ring: 2px border + 3px shadow</div>
                <div style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;">Border: #006AFF | Shadow: rgba(0,106,255,0.15)</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="tab-trap-note" class="doc-h3">Tab Trap Note</h3>
            <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:16px 20px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.15);border-radius:12px;">
              <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text);line-height:1.6;margin:0;"><strong>Important:</strong> By default, <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Tab</code> inserts indentation rather than moving focus. Provide a documented keyboard escape (e.g. <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Escape</code> then <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Tab</code>) for keyboard-only users who need to exit the editor. Optionally expose a setting to use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Tab</code> for focus navigation instead of indentation.</p>
            </div>
